### Wallet API — Test Requests
### Requires the "REST Client" VS Code extension (humao.rest-client)
### Run each block with the "Send Request" button that appears above it.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Create Wallet (Alice)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Expected: 201 Created, walletId in response (save this as walletA)
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. Create Wallet (Bob)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Expected: 201 Created (save walletId as walletB)
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Deposit into Alice's Wallet
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Replace 1 with Alice's actual walletId
### Expected: 200 OK, balance = 1000.0000
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets/1/deposit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 1000.00
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. Transfer from Alice to Bob
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Replace fromWalletId and toWalletId with actual values
### Expected: 200 OK, type = "TRANSFER"
POST {{baseUrl}}/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromWalletId": 1,
  "toWalletId": 2,
  "amount": 250.00
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. Get Balance — Alice
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Expected: 200 OK, balance = 750.0000
GET {{baseUrl}}/wallets/1/balance

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. Get Balance — Bob
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Expected: 200 OK, balance = 250.0000
GET {{baseUrl}}/wallets/2/balance

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. Transaction History — Alice
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
### Expected: 200 OK, array with DEPOSIT + TRANSFER entries
GET {{baseUrl}}/wallets/1/transactions

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Error Cases — verify your exception handler works
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### 404 — wallet doesn't exist
GET {{baseUrl}}/wallets/9999/balance

###

### 422 — insufficient funds (transfer more than balance)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromWalletId": 1,
  "toWalletId": 2,
  "amount": 999999.00
}

###

### 400 — same wallet transfer
POST {{baseUrl}}/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromWalletId": 1,
  "toWalletId": 1,
  "amount": 100.00
}

###

### 400 — validation error (negative amount)
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets/1/deposit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": -50.00
}

###

### 400 — validation error (invalid email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/wallets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Charlie",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}
